postcontent: This Advanced Armament Co (AAC) AR-15 Barrel Assembly is perfect for the shooter who wishes to build or convert an AR-15 to chamber the new 300 AAC Blackout round in order to take advantage of its unique ballistic characteristics. The barrel is finished inside and out with a highly durable and corrosion resistant Black Nitride, a treatment that produces an extremely hard, slick surface on the steel that resists carbon adhesion for easier cleaning and maintenance. The Nitride process converts the steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all of the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering the accuracy degradation commonly encountered with it due to the uneven application of chrome inside a barrel's bore.  This 16" barrel features a 1 in 7" twist and is threaded 5/8"-24 at the muzzle for easy installation of flash hiders, muzzle brakes, and/or sound suppressors. It utilizes the versatile carbine length gas system, a good choice for this cartridge if various weights and types of ammunition are to be used. Most subsonic and supersonic loads, fired from either a suppressed or unsuppressed gun, are compatible with this configuration. However, some subsonic ammunition may not always cycle reliably under adverse conditions or in a severely fouled firearm without a sound suppressor attached to provide extra backpressure. Barrel assembly includes a carbine gas tube, low profile steel gas block, barrel extension and locator pin. Overview

The imageRUNNER 2200 offers unsurpassed performance in standalone or networked environments. Offering Scan-Once-Print-Many technology, standard Automatic Trayless Duplexing, a standard paper capacity of 1,050 sheets (upgradeable to 4,550 sheets), and the most extensive finishing capabilities in its class, the imageRUNNER 2200 truly stands apart from competitive offerings.

Features
The imageRUNNER 2200 features a 22 page-per-minute copy and print speed and a duty cycle of up to 75,000 impressions per month.
A 5.1GB Image Server and 128MB of RAM support a number of key applications including Scan-Once-Print-Many, Confidential Mailboxes, Automatic Page Impositioning, Copy Reservation, and Job Build. These functions can be easily accessed through a large Touchscreen LCD panel at the device.

The standard 1,050-sheet paper capacity can be increased to a maximum of 4,550-sheets through optional accessories. In addition, an Envelope Feeder Attachment is available for high-volume envelope printing environments.
Canon's patented RAPID Fusing System™ dramatically reduces energy consumption costs while virtually eliminating long warm-up periods typically associated with conventional solutions.
A compact engine design makes the imageRUNNER 2200 a perfect fit even in environments with limited space.
With optional network connectivity capable of handling 10/100 Ethernet or Token Ring connections, and support for PostScript® 3 Emulation and PCL® 6 print languages, the imageRUNNER 2200 meets the needs of even the most demanding workgroup environments.

Network scanning capabilities are available through the implementation of Canon's Network ScanGear TWAIN-compliant scanner software. For advanced scanning and file management functionality, the imageRUNNER 2200 supports eCopy Suite, including eCopy ScanStation, eCopy ShareScan, eCopy Desktop and eCopy Viewer.
An optional 50-sheet Duplexing Automatic Document Feeder accepts double-sided originals in sizes up to 11"x 17" and even handles different sized originals to make quick work of multi-page originals.
The imageRUNNER 2200 offers finishing capabilities previously available only through outsourcing or through Central Reproduction Departments. title: For Sale:  Dealer Services
postcontent:
Hello,

I am a private FFL dealer located in northeast Nebraska, specifically South Sioux City. I am putting this ad up to generate some business interest and help out my fellow 2nd amendment supporters. If you are looking for any firearms, optics, reloading supplies including powder, or anything related, I'll do my best to locate and provide competitive price points. I don't have much stock right now but will be adding as time goes on. Availability continues to be volitle and very unpredictable in some areas notably .22 rim fire as well as certain specific weapons. Others are plentiful and reasonably priced. I can also do transfers and welcome transfer requests. I'll charge a reasonable fee. After all, the ATF expects us to operate as a business and keeping them happy seems like good business sense.

I've talked to many folks at the dealer as well as the wholesale level and the consensus is most of the .22 ammo is going to the big box retainers who do business directly with the manufactures. Most local gun stores, myself included do business with distributers who are telling me time and time again that they are not seeing it in any appreciable quantities. 

Despite this, I've managed to find quantities of .22 and can get some to resale. I will not gouge and will say up front that anything I find will be available for a penny per round above what I end up paying. I don't buy junk and refuse to pay unreasonable prices just to say I found some. That being said, specific brands or favorites my or may not be available. I can't get case quantities and will spread out what I can get. 

Thanks for taking the time to read and God Bless

Brian

postcontent:
For sale is a good condition Swedish Mauser chambered in 6.5x55 Swedish. This rifle is commonly called a model M96/38 since it was originally a 29" barreled M96 that was later converted to the handier 24" barreled M38. The receiver for the rifle was manufactured by Carl Gustaf in 1902 using high-end machine tool quality Swedish steel. 

The receiver, bolt, bolt handle, bolt release, barrel bands, magazine floor plate, and butt plate all have matching serial numbers.The stock, metal, and bore are all in good condition, although most of the bluing is missing. The rifle shoots very well; uses a fast cycling "cock on closing" action;  and is capable of producing groups as tight as the shooter can manage. The 6.5 Swedish round is perhaps the best all around rifle cartridge of that era with its mild recoil, excellent ballistic coefficient, and favorable sectional density.

Asking $425 or best offer. More pictures available upon request.

first pump specifically designed for the .410 bore, hammerless, 2 1/2 (introduced 1935) or 3 in. chamber, 26 or 28 in. barrel, plain walnut pistol grip stock with circular grooved forearm (modified 1947), invented by William Roemer, approx. 6 1/2 - 7 lbs. Approx. 164,800 mfg. in 4 grades between 1933-1963.
Add 40% to any Model 42 chambered for 2 1/2 in. shells.
Add 25% for factory installed Cutts compensator (no choke marking on barrel).
Add 25% for pre-war guns.
Subtract 50% for non-factory installed Cutts compensator (choke marked on barrel).
Special order features on field guns have captured much collector interest in recent years. Combinations of these features can add a considerable percentage to the base values listed. Special orders on rare variations are very desirable, and prices can double, or more than double, if the combination is right.
A note on Model 42 Vent. Ribs:
Early Model 42 vent. ribs were designed "Winchester Special Ventilated Rib" circa 1954 in the 125,000 ser. no. range. This rib had a wavy line matting on top of the rib, no stamping on the side, is known as the "Doughnut" post rib, and were in production until the end of 1957 with approx. ser. no. 149,000. The second variation Model 42 rib appears on guns in the approx. ser. no. range 141,000-149,000. This rib was made with both solid and hollow round posts. All parts for the vent. rib were made at the Winchester plant. A third variation was introduced at the end of 1957, when Winchester decided to send its Model 42 barrels to the Simmons Gun Specialty Co. in Kansas City for installation of the vent. ribs. In-the-white barrels were proofed in New Haven and marked on the left side so that the rib would not cover up the proofmark before shipment to Simmons. The ser. no. was not stamped on the receiver extension until the gun was completely assembled. This last variation, or oval post, appears on Model 42s starting at approx. ser. no. 150,000. This third variation is marked either "SIMMONS PATENTED" or "SIMMONS GUN SPECIALTY CO., KANSAS CITY, MO". The longer Simmons marking was stamped on the rib until the end of production.
  Model 42 Slide Action Standard Grade	Add to Collection
26 or 28 in. plain, solid rib or vent. rib (after market) barrel, plain walnut straight or pistol grip stock, walnut grooved forearm. Mfg. 1933-1963.

title: For Sale:  Barrett M107A1 50 cal Sniper Rifle Complete With Nightforce Scope & BORS System
postcontent:
Barrett M107A1 50 cal + possible ammo deal (see below)

I am selling a Barrett M107A1 sniper rifle to help fund my next firearms project.
I have a couple of them so I'm not desperate to sell so please don't think I will take some lowball offer

I have successfully shot steel targets at 1800+ yards with both 660gr & 760gr bullets and have found this setup to be consistently accurate.

I purchased the gun new and added the Nightforce scope and the Barrett BORS system.

The gun has been properly broke in according to manufacturers specifications.

My wife is 5'3" 110lbs and she enjoys shooting this gun. There is minimal recoil.

I am willing to sell the rifle for $10,000.00 without the scope and BORS system or for $13,500.00 as shown.

The rifle itself retails for $14,000.00 the scope was over $2,000.00 and the BORS and mount was around $2,000.00 as well so the price is a good one for this setup.

I have over 1300 rounds of ammo that I am willing to make a deal on as well. It will be much less than it costs in the store.

Barretts BORS Information


LEAVE NOTHING TO CHANCE.
The Barrett Optical Ranging System (BORS) is an integrated ballistics computer that mounts directly on the riflescope and couples to the elevation knob.

BORS instantly takes care of the data work by drawing from several tables and taking into account a number of real-time external factors so you can focus on the task of achieving first round hits.

After determining the range to target, simply turn the elevation knob until the BORS screen matches your target's distance. Internal sensors automatically calculate the ballistic solution. BORS compensates for temperature and barometric pressure, calculates angle cosine and displays rifle cant.

BORS
The BORS kit includes the proprietary Barrett Ballistic PC Software that's pre-programmed with a library selected by Barrett. BORS USB data cable allows the transfer of user programmable custom loads to BORS from his or her computer.

Designed primarily to withstand military operations, BORS is rugged and able to operate with a variety of scopes, calibers and rifles.
